"689","SUPPLEMENT DATED AUGUST 11, 2016 TO THE SUMMARY PROSPECTUSES,"
"690","PROSPECTUSES AND STATEMENTS OF ADDITIONAL INFORMATION DATED"
"691","MAY 1, 2016 FOR LEGG MASON OPPORTUNITY TRUST AND"
"692","FEBRUARY 1, 2016 FOR MILLER INCOME OPPORTUNITY TRUST"
"693","On August 11, 2016, Legg Mason, Inc. (Legg Mason) announced a"
"694","definitive agreement to sell Legg Mason's ownership stake in LMM LLC"
"695","(LMM) to Bill Miller. Currently, 50% of LMM is owned by Legg Mason"
"696","and 50% of LMM is owned, directly and indirectly, by Mr. Miller and an"
"697","entity controlled by him. LMM serves as the investment manager to Legg"
"698","Mason Opportunity Trust, a series of Legg Mason Investment Trust, and"
"699","as subadviser to Miller Income Opportunity Trust, a series of Legg"
"700","Mason Global Asset Management Trust. The transaction is targeted to"
"701","close (the Closing) at the end of 2016, but is subject to certain"
"702","conditions, and may be delayed or may not close under certain"
"703","circumstances."
"704","In connection with the transaction, each fund's Board of Trustees and"
"705","shareholders will be asked to approve the reorganization of such fund"
"706","into a new fund (not affiliated with Legg Mason) for which LMM will"
"707","serve as investment adviser after the Closing, thereby maintaining the"
"708","continuity of each fund's investment program. The portfolio management"
"709","teams of each fund are expected to be the same after the Closing and"
"710","such fund's reorganization."
"711","Subject to Board approval, special meetings of the funds' shareholders"
"712","will be held to consider the fund reorganizations and such other"
"713","matters as the Board may deem appropriate. Before the special"
"714","meetings, shareholders of the funds will receive a combined"
"715","prospectus/proxy statement that discusses the fund reorganizations and"
"716","other matters. The Closing will have the effect of terminating LMM's"
"717","investment management agreement for Legg Mason Opportunity Trust and"
"718","subadvisory agreement for Miller Income Opportunity Trust under the"
"719","Investment Company Act of 1940."
